    "body": "### Problem\n\nSee images below. The window still believes it is maximised if you look at the top right.\n\n<img width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/01357d69-f2e4-4bbf-9464-285d2efeccdc\" />\n\n<img width=\"1920\" height=\"1080\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9fa67095-ce87-446c-86e2-1ee2ecb7f7c8\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nOpen Windows trerminal\n`:restart`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nFor the Window to remain the same size\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nWindows Terminal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nwinget",
